# perimeter

- _perimeter(aGeometry)_

Answer the perimeter of the two-dimensional _aGeometry_.

At `Circle`:

```
>>> Circle([0 0], 1).perimeter
2.pi
```

At `Rectangle`:

```
>>> Rectangle([-1 -1], [1 1]).perimeter
8
```

